1) Raw verbatim transcription (transcriber's internal output):

My dear brothers and sisters, we meet as we mourn the death of our beloved President Russell M. Nelson. I speak to you as the President of the Quorum of the Twelve, in which position I have been sustained in each of our ward, stake, and general conferences for the past seven and a half years. We now go forward with this semi-annual general conference, proceeding as planned and with speakers and music assigned by President Nelson after months of preparation. The only additions are my introductory explanation and my speaking in place of President Nelson in the closing session on Sunday afternoon. This is the first time in about 75 years that a church president has died a few days before a general conference. That has called for us to plan how we could hold the vital leadership meetings in connection with general conference as well as this general session of conference at the same time scheduling his funeral as soon as possible. President Nelson understood the value of general conference to provide direction to the saints in the coming months. We honor him by following the planned conference schedule he approved. In this time of grief we have already held a meeting to pay tribute to President Russell and Nelson before our general conference meetings and then scheduled his funeral as soon as possible after conference. All of this has been done with the approval of the family of President Nelson and the Quorum of the Twelve. Since all of us who have been assigned to speak in general conference would like to devote our assigned time to paying a personal tribute to President Nelson. We have therefore asked that all of our conference speakers hold any such tributes to a minimum deferring elaborate tributes for the funeral which we have already begun to plan. My own brief tribute suitable to this conference and to the tributes we have already paid is this I love Russell M. Nelson and have learned more about the gospel and gospel leadership from my long friendship and association with him than from any other leader I have personally known. He is our model as a servant and follower of the Lord Jesus Christ of these things I testify in the name of Jesus Christ amen.

2) Cleaned, readable transcription for final delivery (speaker labeled):

Speaker: President of the Quorum of the Twelve (Dallin H. Oaks)

My dear brothers and sisters, we meet as we mourn the death of our beloved President Russell M. Nelson. I speak to you as the President of the Quorum of the Twelve, a position I have held for the past seven and a half years. We will proceed with this semi-annual general conference as planned, with speakers and music assigned by President Nelson after months of preparation. The only additions are my introductory explanation and my speaking in place of President Nelson in the closing session on Sunday afternoon. This is the first time in about 75 years that a church president has died just a few days before a general conference. That required planning to hold the vital leadership meetings in connection with general conference, as well as this general session, while scheduling his funeral as soon as possible. President Nelson understood the value of general conference to provide direction to the saints in the coming months. We honor him by following the conference schedule he approved. In this time of grief, we have already held a meeting to pay tribute to President Russell M. Nelson before our general conference meetings, and we have scheduled his funeral as soon as possible after conference. All of this has been done with the approval of President Nelson's family and the Quorum of the Twelve. Because many assigned speakers would like to devote their time to personal tributes, we have asked that all conference speakers keep such tributes brief and defer elaborate tributes to the funeral, which we are planning. My own brief tribute, suitable to this conference and to the tributes already given, is this: I love Russell M. Nelson. From my long friendship and association with him, I have learned more about the gospel and gospel leadership than from any other leader I have known. He is our model as a servant and follower of the Lord Jesus Christ. Of these things I testify, in the name of Jesus Christ, amen.

3) Short summary

Key points:
- The speaker addresses the congregation following the death of President Russell M. Nelson.
- The semi-annual general conference will proceed as planned; only an introductory explanation and the speaker filling the closing role have been added.
- This is the first time in about 75 years a church president has died just before general conference, requiring coordination of conference meetings and the funeral.
- A tribute meeting was held before conference; the funeral has been scheduled soon after conference with family and Quorum approval.
- Conference speakers were asked to keep personal tributes brief and defer longer tributes to the funeral.
- The speaker offers a personal testimony regarding President Nelson's example and leadership.

Action items:
- Proceed with the semi-annual general conference schedule as approved by President Nelson.
- Hold the scheduled funeral as soon as possible after conference (planning in progress).
- Conference speakers should limit personal tributes during conference and reserve extended tributes for the funeral.

Decisions:
- The Church will follow the planned conference schedule approved by President Nelson.
- The speaker will provide an introductory explanation and will speak in place of President Nelson in the closing session.
- The funeral timing and arrangements will proceed with approval of President Nelson's family and the Quorum of the Twelve.

